Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian/Library Technician Vancouver , BC Description Salaried position with benefits: 30 hours per week (typically M-Th; 10am-6pm)Overall Responsibility: Manages all library operations and leads a team of committed professionals and volunteers in order to create a welcoming, inclusive and comfortable place in which members of the Jewish and non-Jewish community can pursue educational, informational and social interests by providing a wide range of print and electronic Judaic resources to serve their needs. Key Areas of Responsibility Administration Manage day to day operations in the libraryPlan for the overall development of the library including policy and planning (annual workplan, budgeting, etc.).Maintain and collect statistics, reports, correspondence Manage logistics related to f book donations, processing, selecting, storing, etc.Coordinate ongoing consultations with maintenance re: used books/cleaning/storage Supervise, coordinate and train library staff and volunteers (includes recruitment, hiring, motivation and appreciation)
Library Services Collection development &amp; acquisitions Circulation services Reference and information services Program Development Create programs as appropriate to promote goals and values of the Library Facilitate programs and/or support facilitators Encourage local writers, artists and other talents Adapt programming for new technologies Develop programming in other locations &amp; other spaces within the JCC Fundraising Coordinate and execute fundraising events including: annual Telethon, Used Book Sale, Read-a-thonGrants: identify opportunities and write grant applications Develop relationships with donors Community engagement and promotion Community outreach &amp; public relations Marketing and promoting the library Social media Cooperation &amp; collaboration with library organizations (public &amp; college libraries; associations: BCLA, AJL) Cooperation &amp; collaboration with Jewish community agencies &amp; organizations Customer Service (organizations and individuals) Engage in outreach initiatives and outlying community activities Liaise and develop collaborations with other JCC Departments Computer and Technical Operations Purchasing, maintaining library hardware, software &amp; networks Database development &amp; maintenance Qualifications An accredited master of Library and Information Services degree. A Library Technician Diploma will also be considered with the right combination of experienceExperience in public libraries &amp; knowledge of standard library services and operations ● Excellent communication and interpersonal skills Knowledge of Jewish customs and traditions Some Hebrew knowledge is an asset Experience working with volunteers Fundraising/ PR experience Budget development and management skills Advanced computer / technical skills Knowledge of current library practices, new technologies and trends The successful candidate must clear a vulnerable sector criminal record check as a condition of employment.Start Date: January 6, 2025 or soonerInterested individuals may apply via our website Compensation $25-$35/hr commensurate with education and experience Closes: 20 January, 2025 Jewish Community Centre of Greater Vancouver Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
