Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Circulation Technician Toronto , ON Description Circulation Technician(This Temporary Full Time Opportunity is available for up to six (6) months.) Competition Number: LA-2024-129 Division: Information and Technology Services Closing Date: December 11, 2024 Branch: Legislative Library Compensation: $58,996.00 - $80,232.00 Position Type: Contract Full-time Are you ready to embark on an extraordinary journey to shape the future of Ontario's Legislative Assembly, with innovation and excellence in parliamentary operations? At the Office of the Assembly, we're not just supporting Parliament; we’re a dynamic team dedicated to driving change and making an impact every day.At the heart of our mission is to provide non-partisan administrative and procedural services to all MPPs, along with operational support for the daily activities of the Legislative Assembly of Ontario. Our success is intricately tied to the strength and diversity of our staff, as we champion our core values: integrity, inclusiveness, collaboration, and excellence.Looking for a rewarding career where you can share your expertise in a Circulation Technician capacity? Seize this opportunity to embody our organizational values within our Legislative Library Branch. As a valued member of our team, reporting directly to the Supervisor, Circulation and News, you will play a significant role as the first impression clients will have of the Branch by receiving their calls, greeting visitors, and providing exceptional customer service to Members of the Provincial Parliament (MPPs), officers and staff of the Assembly. You will also support the branch by playing a role in building the Library’s collection ofresources (e.g. press releases) archiving them to the Library’s digital repository, processing for documents shelving, and/or making them discoverable through the online catalogue.
What You’ll DoYou’ll act with integrity to:Interact with MPPs and their staff, retrieving materials, and handling circulation transactions using an integrated library system (ILS)Provide basic research assistance in a fast-paced environment to clients and reference support to Research Librarians and Research Officers, performing searches in print and electronic news sources such as Lexis Nexis, ProQuest, etc. Assist with stack maintenance and shelving, update loose-leaf services, and process interlibrary loansAssist with receiving, check-in and processing of Parliamentary and Sessional Papers, and Election Finance materialAssist with pickup and delivery to/from other libraries, local bookstores or organizationsDownload publications (e.g. party press release)from the internet and archive to the library’s digital repository, following the Library’s collection policyCreate original descriptive cataloguing records for publications (e.g. party press releases)following international standards, such as RDA and MARC 21, and in-house policiesOffer suggestions related to collection management, including recommended discards of little-used and outdated material.You’ll support our collaboration as you:Are able to work both independently and collaboratively in a well-established team environmentAre a highly motivated self-starter with excellent interpersonal skills, the ability to work independently or in a team and the flexibility and other skills needed to serve a client group with frequently changing priorities and tight deadlinesMay be required to undertake occasional assignments outside the Circulation &amp; News Services unit in addition to your primary responsibilities, such as collaborating with others on branch/division teams or special projectsHow You QualifyYou demonstrate excellence through your:Completion of a college diploma (a recognized library techniques program or equivalent is preferred) and up to 2 years of prior related /on-the-job experience.Demonstrated advanced reading comprehension, attention to detail, strong organizational skills, flexibility, and demonstrated experience working under pressureProficiency in relevant computer technology systems and software applications Experience working with Ex Libris (Alma/Primo) (would be an asset)Service orientation, well-developed communication, organizational, analytical and interpersonal skills, demonstrated experience working under pressure, flexibility to multi-task in response to clients’ changing priorities and deadlinesEnthusiasm and motivation, ability to work independently and collaboratively as part of the team to solve problems, share and communicate knowledgeHere’s what awaits you:A dynamic, unique work environmentA team of dedicated professionalsSupport for your career through training and development Access to an employee and family assistance programIf you’re ambitious, passionate, and ready to make your mark, seize the opportunity by visiting us at www.ola.org and selecting “Careers” at the bottom of the page for more details.Join us in shaping the future of Ontario's Legislative Assembly. Your journey starts here!The Legislative Assembly of Ontario is proud to be an equal opportunity employer who champions diversity and inclusion. We foster an environment where unique perspectives are valued, ensuring that everyone has the opportunity to make a meaningful impact. If you need accommodations during the application process, please don’t hesitate to reach out to us at hr@ola.org.While we appreciate your interest in obtaining employment with the Legislative Assembly of Ontario, only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $58,996.00 - $80,232.00 per annum Closes: 11 December, 2024 Legislative Assembly of Ontario Toronto , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
