Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Research Librarian Moncton , NB Description Department: George A. Rawlyk LibraryContract: Full TimeStart Date: May 1, 2025 (pending budgetary approval)Job Summary:The Research Librarian guides students and faculty through the research process so they can use the resources and services of the George A. Rawlyk Library to maximal advantage in their scholarly endeavours. This position manages Crandall’s research and data management (RDM) workflow as well as the instructional and outreach activities of the library.The position is responsible for engaging in library activities outside the walls of the library’s physical space, both on and off campus, and both in person and online. These activities include teaching students how to do library research, creating online research aids, and generating excitement about what the library has to offer. The position also helps inform the University Librarian’s administrative decisions by gathering statistics and writing reports relating to the library collection, library technologies, library usage, and Crandall-related research outputs.Key Duties:Oversees Crandall’s institutional RDM activities and technologies; supports faculty in their research; and tracks publications relating to Crandall and its students, staff, and facultyManages the library’s technologies by serving as the technology contact for vendors; reporting on updates to the integrated library system; engaging in embedded librarianship; and maintaining the library’s website, research guides, and social mediaGenerates excitement and interest about the library’s resources and services by creating advertisements, planning events, collaborating with other departments, and making targeted recommendations to individualsGathers statistics to monitor various library features including electronic resource usage; physical collection development; reference interview characteristics; and gate countsOversees the instructional activities of the library including delivering library orientation sessions, presenting library technology workshops, and creating online library tutorialsQualifications &amp; Skills:Master of Library Science degree or equivalent is required.Additional graduate degree in a discipline taught at Crandall would be an asset.Excellent research skills, interpersonal skills, and organizational skillsExcellent communication skills in English, both written and verbalStrong attention to detailCommitment to excellence in serving faculty, staff, and studentsStrong computer skills in Microsoft Office suite, especially in ExcelExperience with instruction, event planning, and online library systemsExperience with LibGuides, WorldShare Management Services, and COUNTER 5 would be an assetAbility to work effectively both independently and as part of a cross-functional teamAbility to learn new technologies and proceduresAbility to evaluate materials visuallyAccuracy and efficiency in performing repetitive tasksDemonstrated commitment to the mission of the University of “transforming lives through quality university education firmly rooted in the Christian faith”The Application Process:In accordance with Canadian immigration regulations, this advertisement is addressed first to Canadian citizens and permanent residents. Crandall University is committed to excellence in its hiring practices, and will accept internal and external applicants in seeking the most qualified candidate.Crandall University is a growing Christian university offering baccalaureate degrees in Arts, Business Administration, Science, Organizational Management and Education and master degrees in Education and Management. Located in Moncton, New Brunswick, Canada, it was established by and is sponsored by the Canadian Baptists of Atlantic Canada. Crandall University is provincially chartered to grant degrees and certificates for undergraduate and graduate programs and serves students from across Canada and around the world.To be considered for appointment, candidates must demonstrate an understanding of and freely embrace the University’s Mission Statement and Statement of Faith. Short listed candidates will receive copies of these two documents prior to the interview.Salary: Librarian Level 1 ($54,930 – $ 72,480); placement on scale based on experienceApplication deadline: February 1, 2025. Competition will remain open until the position is filled.Please forward curriculum vitae, cover letter, and contact information for three references to:The Hiring Manager. careers@crandallu.caPlease use the following in the subject line of the email: Ref: CU202407002 Application for the role of Research Librarian.We thank all applicants for their interest, but please note that only those selected for an interview will be contacted. Compensation $54,930 – $ 72,480 Closes: 1 February, 2025 Crandall University Moncton , NB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
